# Project Structure

Keep `src/app/` focused on routing, pages, and UI. Put reusable code in the appropriate `src/` subfolder.

## `src/` — domain folders

| Kind | Location |
| --- | ---- |
| Pure helpers, formatters, mappers | `src/utils/` |
| React hooks | `src/hooks/` |
| Shared TypeScript types | `src/types/` |
| Shared React components | `src/components/` |
| Third-party wrappers, integrations | `src/lib/` |
| App configuration | `src/config/` |
| Shared constants | `src/constants/` |
| Validation schemas | `src/schemas/` |
| React contexts | `src/contexts/` |
| State reducers | `src/reducers/` |
| HTTP clients, API helpers | `src/http/` |
| Global styles, design tokens | `src/styles/` |

- ✅ Good:

  ```
  src/utils/group-by.ts
  src/hooks/use-form-state/use-form-state.ts
  src/types/optional.ts
  src/styles/globals.css
  ```

- ❌ Bad:

  ```
  src/app/group-by.ts
  src/app/use-form-state.ts
  src/app/globals.css
  ```

## `src/app/` — Next.js app shell only

The App Router folder is for:

- **Pages**: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`
- **Route-local components**: colocated UI under feature folders
- **Framework entry points**: `app/api/`

Do **not** add standalone utility modules or global styles in `src/app/`.

## `src/` layout

```
src/
├── app/                # App Router — pages, route UI
│   ├── page.tsx
│   └── layout.tsx
├── styles/
│   └── globals.css
├── utils/
├── hooks/
├── types/
└── ...
```

When logic is reused outside one route, move it to the matching `src/<domain>/` folder.
